annotation.TEXT: Here, I'm rapidly tapping up like a madman, even if that's not necessary.

Okay, you may not have seen any transition effect here, but I just went back and searched Mole Cave top to bottom, and I couldn't find any golden berries or any other secrets, so I scrapped that part of the recording entirely.
WHOA, HOLY CRAP!!! It's a Banzai Mole!
Who the heck are you? Some kind of Ninji impersonator?
That tiny dead-end looks suspicious...
Oh, it doesn't look like I can make that jump, though.
...Assuming the game will let me go to the right...
Wow, why does such a jump have to be so tricky?
Whoa, hello! I had no idea that 1-up was there! I only moved that way to quickly recenter the camera.
Huh, a save prompt. Okay. Now, I certainly have time for another level, so let's check out Mole Hole! (Gee... I wonder what kind of enemy I'll encounter here...)
Huh. A P-switch... I wonder what it does...
Huh. That's an odd glitch. I wonder why the eating block stopped short like that?
Okay, I'm not touching that P-switch again!
So, how do I exit? Oh, that's how.
Do I have to hit the P-switch? I'll have to wait for it to expire before I can move again after hitting it, but maybe it'll cause a springboard to fall or something.
Those two red dots are always watching you...
That was another dirty trick...
Whoa! Good thing I was holding right there!
By the way, what's with the unreachable moles in the dirt? Maybe they're just there to make it look more like their home.
Hmm... I'm suspicious... Is this big guy hiding anything? (Probably, since I haven't found this level's golden berry yet.)

This music sounds like it's from Donkey Kong 64. Maybe it's from Banjo-Kazooie instead, but I'm really leaning towards DK64. (It is indeed from DK64-- It's "Puzzles in the Caves". Thanks, TheGoomba98.)
Hmm... Well, let me screen-scroll over while I wait...
Okay, so forget the P-switch. What else can I do here?
Gold berry count: 3
Well, I'm not seeing any coins or brown blocks, so I don't see any reason for that evil ? block wall to have been placed back there...
There's only enough room in this hack for one Ninji, and that's me! (Well, I suppose there's enough room for any friendly/allied Ninjis too, if there are any.)

If anybody does know where a golden berry is in Mole Hole, let me know! In the meantime, it looks like the next level will perhaps be a true water level, which I'll be playing next time! To be continued...

I'm rapidly jumping in these narrow passages just in case there's a secret passage above me at some point. (Though, knowing my luck, I'll probably miss the one spot that actually does have a secret passage!)
So, let's check out the Fungus Swamp.
Ooh, right away I recognize this music. It's the temple theme from Donkey Kong Land.
Oh, come on! Really, game?! Really?! What is this, Syobon Action or Eryi's Action?
Aha! Hidden 1-up!
And of course, now I'm going to want to check every platform for hidden 1-ups!
Okay, you're not fooling me here again, game!
There's two 1-ups, but no golden berry? Well, maybe it's to the right...
Greetings, everyone, and welcome back, to NINJI! JUMP! ALPHAAAAA!!!
Demo count: 5
Demo count: 6
Whoa! Gotta be more patient.
Whoa, don't glitch on me now!
You are no match for me, Chuck!
Wow, it felt like I just barely cleared that gap.
Interesting how I emerged, there.
Well, I didn't see anything resembling a golden berry in this level, and I was told each level had one, so I think I'll go back and look for it...
Well, it's nice to know you can stand on the big guy. Also, there's totally a secret here!
I'd better scout ahead, just so I can see where this is going.
Well, that level had its tricky points, but it went way better than the first level did!
And that just returns me to the regular path. I hope the big guy isn't in front of me.
OMNOMNOM!
Ludicrous speed for the P-switch waiting!
Oh, this is so an eating block thing, and that is so my golden berry!
Okay, finally, I am now free to move about the country.
Die, Yoshi!
And of course, there's the springboard, like I guessed. But, why put this ? block wall here? Is there something in the near future that having the P-switch active would screw up?
Oh, good. The sprite limit has decided to come and help me out a little bit.
More danmaku, in the form of baseballs this time. Well, this should be no problem for me to handle!
This version of this song definitely uses different instruments than the one I'm used to hearing.
Whoa! Okay, I'd better stop fooling around before I get myself killed!
GAAAAAMMMEEE!!!
Oh, man. Without being able to run or spin jump, Lava Lotus could be a huge threat!
Whoa, what is this, a danmaku game all of a sudden?
Yeah, big surprise. Also, there's loose spikes for some reason.
Since the first block was technically the eating block sprite itself, landing on it doesn't activate it. I have to actually land on one of the other brown blocks to start it up.
Those two red dots are forever unblinking...
They're totally doing this on purpose just to drive me nuts.
Fast-forward!
